Pronotum metazona distally flattened, squared, with strait or shallowly concave posterior margin. SGP (
Fig. 19B
) short; wider than long; convex on the apex. Ovipositor (
Fig. 19A
) strait on the base and regularly falciform after the base; without denticulations; apex pointing; 7.3 ± 0.45 (min: 6.5; max: 7.8) times as long (apex to base of the ventral margin) as ovipositor median width.

